```text
Time Limit: 1 sec
Memory: 256 MB

Description

You are given an array of N integers arr. You need to check if it contains at least 2 elements which differ by 1.

Input Format

The first line of the input contains one integer T - the number of test cases.

For each test case:

- The first line contains the integer N.
- The second line contains N space-separated integers:
  arr1, arr2, ..., arrN.

Output Format

For each test case, print "yes" if a pair satisfying the given condition is present in arr, otherwise print "no".

Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 10^3

1 ≤ N ≤ 10^5

0 ≤ arri ≤ 10^9

It is guaranteed that the sum of N over all test cases does not exceed 10^6.

Sample Input 1

1
5
11 1 8 12 14

Sample Output 1

yes

Sample Input 2

1
5
1 3 5 7 10

Sample Output 2

no

Note

In Sample Input 1:

The array contains 11 and 12, which differ by 1.

Therefore, the output is:

yes

In Sample Input 2:

No pair of elements in the array differs by 1.

Therefore, the output is:

no
```


#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
typedef long long ll;
#define endl "\n"   // optional, better to avoid redefining endl

bool comp(const pair<string,int>&a, const pair<string,int>&b)
{
    return a.second < b.second;
}
void solve() {
   int n;
   cin>>n;
   vector<int>v(n);
   for(int i = 0 ; i < n ; i++) cin>>v[i];
   sort(v.begin(),v.end());
   int cnt = 0;
   for(int i = 1; i < n ; i++)
   {
    if(abs(v[i] - v[i-1]) == 1)
    {
        cnt++;
    }
   }
   if(cnt)
   {
    cout<<"yes"<<endl;
   }
   else
   {
    cout<<"no"<<endl;
   }

}

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);
      int t;
      cin>>t;
      while(t--)
      {
        solve();
      }
    

    return 0;
}



